WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.606 --> 01:02.129
Be careful, your fingers.

01:22.149 --> 01:23.672
May I help you?

01:23.759 --> 01:27.981
This is the Calthorpe.
Private hotel.

01:28.068 --> 01:30.244
I'm Mrs. Eleanor Young.

01:30.331 --> 01:33.813
I have a reservation
at the Lancaster Suite.

01:33.900 --> 01:37.425
We spoke on the phone
when I confirmed yesterday.

01:37.512 --> 01:40.820
Sorry, don't seem to have
your reservation.

01:42.343 --> 01:43.866
Good evening.

01:43.953 --> 01:45.694
I'm Reginald Ormsby,

01:45.781 --> 01:48.001
hotel manager.
Is there a problem?

01:48.088 --> 01:49.959
I'm Mrs. Eleanor Young.

01:50.046 --> 01:53.398
My family and I would like
to be shown to our suite.

01:53.485 --> 01:55.356
We've had a long flight.

01:55.443 --> 01:59.055
We're fully booked, madam.
You must have made a mistake.

01:59.142 --> 02:00.753
I'm sure
you and your lovely family

02:00.840 --> 02:03.059
can find other accommodation.

02:03.146 --> 02:06.454
May I suggest
you explore Chinatown?

02:13.200 --> 02:16.116
Please, may I use
your phone to call my husband?

02:16.203 --> 02:18.336
It's the least you can do.

02:18.945 --> 02:20.294
Mmm.

02:27.649 --> 02:29.869
Mrs. Young,
I must ask you to leave

02:29.956 --> 02:31.131
or I'll have to call
the police.

02:31.218 --> 02:33.046
Please, go right ahead.

02:35.962 --> 02:38.965
Lord Calthorpe, my apologies
for the disturbance.

02:39.052 --> 02:43.926
Eleanor! I just got off
the phone with your husband.

02:44.013 --> 02:46.364
Get the Lancaster Suite ready.
Now.

02:47.756 --> 02:49.497
Surely you're joking, sir.

02:49.584 --> 02:51.717
I assure you, I'm not.

02:51.804 --> 02:53.414
As of this evening,

02:53.501 --> 02:55.808
my family's long history

02:55.895 --> 03:00.160
as custodians
of the Calthorpe is ended.

03:00.247 --> 03:03.293
I'm selling the hotel
to my dear friends,

03:03.381 --> 03:05.644
the Young family of Singapore.

03:07.036 --> 03:09.778
Meet the new lady
of the house,

03:09.865 --> 03:11.301
Eleanor Young.

03:13.086 --> 03:14.435
Join me for a toast.

03:14.522 --> 03:16.089
We'd be delighted.

03:20.354 --> 03:23.096
Do get a mop. The floor's wet.

03:29.668 --> 03:31.278
Get a mop.

04:03.441 --> 04:05.486
I'm all in.

04:14.103 --> 04:16.236
Fold.

04:16.322 --> 04:17.803
Oh...

04:17.890 --> 04:19.021
Nothing?

04:20.545 --> 04:22.329
This whole time
you had nothing?

04:23.286 --> 04:24.853
All right, so

04:24.940 --> 04:28.901
how did I beat T.A. Curtis
so very, very badly?

04:28.988 --> 04:32.121
Well, I know for a fact
that Curtis is cheap.

04:33.688 --> 04:36.561
So he's not playing
using logic or math,

04:36.648 --> 04:38.345
but using his psychology.

04:38.432 --> 04:41.043
Our brains so hate the idea

04:41.130 --> 04:42.741
of losing something
that's valuable to us

04:42.828 --> 04:44.351
that we abandon
all rational thought,

04:44.438 --> 04:46.048
and we make some really
poor decisions.

04:46.135 --> 04:47.963
So, Curtis wasn't playing
to win.

04:48.050 --> 04:50.009
He was playing not to lose.

04:50.096 --> 04:52.881
Here.
Put it towards a haircut.

04:54.230 --> 04:56.145
All right,
that's it for today.

04:56.232 --> 04:58.583
Don't forget your essays
on conditional probability

04:58.670 --> 05:00.715
are due next week.

05:10.508 --> 05:12.292
Yes! Mmm-hmm.

05:12.379 --> 05:14.468
You know what?
You can order your own.

05:14.555 --> 05:16.601
Mmm. I'm okay with coffee.
Thanks.

05:16.688 --> 05:18.428
Yeah, well,
you always say that,

05:18.516 --> 05:20.300
and then you end up eating
all my dessert.

05:20.387 --> 05:21.606
I don't know
what you're talking about.

05:21.693 --> 05:23.782
'Cause I have, like,
a tiny bit.

05:23.869 --> 05:25.087
Uh-huh. Okay.
Can we have one more

05:25.174 --> 05:26.524
of these, please? Thank you.

05:28.134 --> 05:31.137
So what about us
taking an adventure east?

05:34.836 --> 05:37.404
You wanna get pork buns
in the East Village.

05:37.491 --> 05:38.623
That's what it is, isn't it?

05:40.363 --> 05:43.715
I was actually thinking
of further east.

05:43.802 --> 05:46.152
Like Queens?

05:46.239 --> 05:48.807
Like Singapore.
For spring break.

05:48.894 --> 05:50.417
Colin's wedding.

05:50.504 --> 05:52.158
We've been dating
for over a year now,

05:52.245 --> 05:53.420
and I think it's about time

05:53.507 --> 05:55.161
people met
my beautiful girlfriend.

05:55.248 --> 05:57.772
Come on, I'm Colin's best man.

05:57.859 --> 05:59.557
Don't you wanna see
where I grew up?

05:59.644 --> 06:02.168
Meet my family, my Ah Ma?

06:02.255 --> 06:04.562
And meet up with that strange
college roommate of yours.

06:04.649 --> 06:06.041
Peik Lin.

06:06.128 --> 06:07.477
- Mmm-hmm. Peik Lin.
- She has been begging me

06:07.565 --> 06:08.957
to come visit her, you know.

06:09.044 --> 06:11.743
The universe has spoken.
It wants you over there.

06:13.092 --> 06:14.833
Come to Singapore.

06:14.920 --> 06:17.792
I want the whole island to
meet the brilliant Rachel Chu.

06:18.532 --> 06:19.620
Aww.

07:36.131 --> 07:38.090
"If then you have
been raised with Christ,

07:39.352 --> 07:40.875
"Seek the things
that are above

07:40.962 --> 07:43.051
"where Christ is seated

07:43.138 --> 07:46.228
"at the right hand of God.

07:46.315 --> 07:49.188
"Set your minds
on things that are above,

07:49.275 --> 07:52.191
"not on things
that are on Earth."

07:52.278 --> 07:54.149
Eleanor,
is Nicki bringing a girl

07:54.236 --> 07:55.803
to Colin's wedding?

07:55.890 --> 07:58.153
My Amanda heard it
from her friend Francesca.

07:58.240 --> 08:00.852
Eddie says
her name is Rachel Chu.

08:00.939 --> 08:03.419
Oh, I thought that
Nick was coming alone.

08:03.506 --> 08:05.683
Did you know
he had a girlfriend?

08:05.770 --> 08:09.295
Nick dates many girls.
It's hard to keep track.

08:09.382 --> 08:10.905
Amanda knows everyone

08:10.992 --> 08:12.994
and she has never heard
of her.

08:13.081 --> 08:14.735
Rachel Chu.

08:14.822 --> 08:17.956
Maybe she's from the Taiwan
plastics Chu family.

08:18.043 --> 08:20.741
If you want,
I have a private investigator.

08:20.828 --> 08:22.308
Very discreet.

08:22.395 --> 08:25.137
I think we should return
to the word of God.

08:26.573 --> 08:27.661
Alix.

08:29.141 --> 08:31.926
Ephesians.
Chapter six, verse four.

08:32.013 --> 08:34.320
"Bring up your children
in the discipline

08:34.407 --> 08:35.842
"and instruction of the Lord."

08:35.929 --> 08:37.409
Oh, I do hope
she's a good Christian girl.

08:37.496 --> 08:38.498
Well,
if he's bringing her home,

08:38.585 --> 08:39.847
it must be serious.

08:39.933 --> 08:40.934
Exactly.

08:45.723 --> 08:47.376
Oh.

08:47.463 --> 08:49.509
- It's my mum. Do you mind?
- Mmm. Go ahead.

08:49.596 --> 08:50.771
All right.

08:50.858 --> 08:52.251
- Save me some of that.
- Okay.

08:54.296 --> 08:56.429
Hey, Mum,
everything okay?

08:56.516 --> 08:59.171
Does something have
to be wrong for me to call?

08:59.258 --> 09:01.521
Yeah, usually.

09:01.608 --> 09:03.610
Very funny.

09:03.697 --> 09:05.264
Are you bringing
the girl you're seeing

09:05.351 --> 09:07.222
to Colin's wedding?

09:07.309 --> 09:10.356
Mmm. We were literally
just talking about that.

09:10.443 --> 09:12.010
How could you know?

09:12.097 --> 09:13.751
Everybody knows.

09:19.626 --> 09:21.715
Radio One Asia.

09:21.802 --> 09:24.413
Move on to Corinthians.
I'll catch up.

09:24.500 --> 09:25.980
Oh, yes.

09:26.067 --> 09:28.374
We're looking forward
to having you home.

09:28.461 --> 09:31.681
And your room
is all ready for you.

09:31.769 --> 09:33.466
Thanks, Mum.

09:33.553 --> 09:35.729
But Rachel and I will be
staying together.

09:35.816 --> 09:37.165
I see.

09:37.252 --> 09:39.472
Well, I'm having
the house re-done.

09:39.559 --> 09:41.387
And it's not ready for guests.

09:41.474 --> 09:43.693
If Rachel comes, I think
she might be more comfortable

09:43.781 --> 09:45.608
staying somewhere else.

09:47.872 --> 09:49.438
All right, sorry about that.

09:49.525 --> 09:50.962
I saved you a piece.

09:51.049 --> 09:53.312
You did, did you?
A very small piece at that.

09:53.399 --> 09:55.227
Thank you very much.

09:55.314 --> 09:58.099
How's your mom?
Everything okay?

09:58.186 --> 10:00.972
Couldn't be better.

10:01.059 --> 10:03.017
Hey, Mom, this one's kind of
cute. What do you think?

10:03.104 --> 10:06.716
No, no! You can't wear that
to meet Nick's Ah Ma.

10:06.804 --> 10:09.328
Blue and white
is for Chinese funerals.

10:09.415 --> 10:14.072
Now this, this symbolizes
good fortune and fertility.

10:14.159 --> 10:17.727
Great! I was really going for
that "lucky baby maker" vibe.

10:17.815 --> 10:19.599
Hey! You're the one
who asked for my help

10:19.686 --> 10:21.340
picking out a dress
to meet Nick's family.

10:21.427 --> 10:23.777
It's only 'cause I hardly know
anything about them.

10:23.864 --> 10:25.866
Every time I bring them up,
Nick changes the subject.

10:25.953 --> 10:27.737
Maybe he's embarrassed.

10:27.825 --> 10:30.001
Maybe his parents are poor,
and he has to send them money.

10:30.088 --> 10:32.133
That's what
all good Chinese children do.

10:32.220 --> 10:33.831
Oh, you're going to have

10:33.918 --> 10:35.528
a wonderful time.

10:35.615 --> 10:37.704
You've always wanted
to go to Asia.

10:37.791 --> 10:40.576
And who knows, if all
goes well in Singapore,

10:40.663 --> 10:42.578
you might just come back
with a souvenir.

10:42.665 --> 10:44.798
Oh, Mom, stop!

10:44.885 --> 10:46.495
Nick and I haven't
even talked about that.

10:48.933 --> 10:51.587
I mean, his parents
can't not like me, right?

10:53.981 --> 10:55.809
What was that look?
I saw that.

10:55.896 --> 10:58.029
Nothing. It's just,

10:58.116 --> 10:59.987
Nick bringing a girl
all the way there

11:00.074 --> 11:01.684
to meet them can mean a lot

11:01.771 --> 11:03.904
to these overseas families.
They're different from us.

11:03.991 --> 11:07.647
How are they different?
They're Chinese, I'm Chinese.

11:07.734 --> 11:10.041
I'm so Chinese,
I'm an economics professor

11:10.128 --> 11:12.173
with lactose intolerance.

11:12.260 --> 11:14.088
Yeah, but you grew up here.

11:21.966 --> 11:23.271
You're different.

11:24.577 --> 11:25.970
But wearing a lucky color

11:26.057 --> 11:29.060
will make
a good first impression.

11:34.674 --> 11:36.328
Okay, game plan.

11:36.415 --> 11:38.373
Check our bags,
get through security,

11:38.460 --> 11:40.288
and then we could eat
one of the three homemade

11:40.375 --> 11:42.551
Tupperware meals
my mom packed for us.

11:42.638 --> 11:44.423
Good afternoon, Mr. Young,
Miss Chu.

11:44.510 --> 11:46.294
We'll take your bags and get
you checked into first class.

11:46.381 --> 11:48.383
- Great.
- Oh. No, there's a mistake.

11:48.470 --> 11:51.169
We're not first class.
We're economy people.

11:51.256 --> 11:52.387
This way, please.

11:52.474 --> 11:54.607
Just go with it. Come on.

11:54.694 --> 11:56.217
But...

11:56.304 --> 11:58.219
Yeah, they'll be fine.
Just leave them there.

12:02.310 --> 12:04.225
Welcome aboard,
Mr. Young, Miss Chu.

12:04.312 --> 12:06.053
Here's the way
to your private suite.

12:07.446 --> 12:09.317
And some champagne.

12:11.580 --> 12:13.147
Thank you.

12:16.672 --> 12:19.197
- Thank you very much.
- You're welcome.

12:19.284 --> 12:21.764
After takeoff, would you like
to enjoy the lounge chairs,

12:21.851 --> 12:23.462
or should we convert
your suite into a bedroom?

12:23.549 --> 12:26.204
Uh... We're good. Thank you.

12:26.291 --> 12:27.292
Enjoy.

12:29.337 --> 12:31.426
- Nick. We can't afford this.
- Mmm.

12:34.386 --> 12:37.998
These pajamas are fancier
than any of my real clothes.

12:38.085 --> 12:39.652
My family has business
with the airline.

12:39.739 --> 12:42.133
The tickets, they're a perk.

12:45.223 --> 12:46.920
What kind of business?

12:47.007 --> 12:49.531
Real estate, investment,
other things.

12:49.618 --> 12:50.793
Nothing interesting.

12:50.880 --> 12:51.881
"Dim sum."

12:54.928 --> 12:58.888
So your family is, like, rich?

12:58.976 --> 13:01.021
We're comfortable.

13:01.108 --> 13:04.329
That is exactly what
a super-rich person would say.

13:06.809 --> 13:08.768
It's not a big deal,
obviously.

13:08.855 --> 13:12.990
I just think it's kind of
weird that I had no idea.

13:13.077 --> 13:15.035
I mean,
you have a Jamba Juice card.

13:15.122 --> 13:17.255
You use my Netflix password.

13:17.342 --> 13:19.779
You play basketball at that Y
that kind of smells.

13:19.866 --> 13:21.868
I really like that place,
thank you very much.

13:23.261 --> 13:25.306
And yes, my family has money,

13:25.393 --> 13:27.134
but I've always
thought of it as theirs.

13:27.221 --> 13:28.614
Not mine.

13:28.701 --> 13:30.268
I get that.
But I'm going all the way

13:30.355 --> 13:32.139
over there to meet them...

13:32.226 --> 13:34.446
Kind of just wanna know
what I'm getting into.

13:34.533 --> 13:36.970
And, you know,
they're your family.

13:37.057 --> 13:38.667
Well...

13:40.669 --> 13:42.280
My family is much like
anybody else's.

13:42.367 --> 13:43.890
Mmm-hmm.

13:43.977 --> 13:45.805
There's half of them
that you love and respect,

13:45.892 --> 13:47.981
and then
there's the other half.

13:48.068 --> 13:49.417
Which half am I meeting?

13:52.942 --> 13:54.379
Well,
there's my cousin Alistair,

13:54.466 --> 13:56.250
based in Taiwan,
works in movies.

13:58.296 --> 13:59.993
And cut!

14:00.080 --> 14:03.779
He's dating Kitty Pong,
an actress.

14:03.866 --> 14:04.911
- Kitty.
- Alistair.

14:06.782 --> 14:10.003
You like it?
I was feeling very,

14:10.090 --> 14:13.441
very the emotions.
Can you feel it?

14:13.528 --> 14:16.575
Oh, I can feel all of you.
And all of me.

14:30.023 --> 14:31.329
Okay, and what
about your cousin Eddie?

14:31.416 --> 14:32.852
You don't ever talk about him.

14:32.939 --> 14:35.246
Well, Eddie's a big
finance guy in Hong Kong.

14:35.333 --> 14:36.464
A real family man.

14:40.294 --> 14:41.382
You know,
if you move,

14:41.469 --> 14:42.862
it will look more natural.

14:42.949 --> 14:45.386
No, this way you get
our optimal angles.

14:45.473 --> 14:47.388
Then we're done.

14:49.042 --> 14:50.652
Russell, thank you so much.

14:50.739 --> 14:52.350
It's an honor
to be photographed by you.

14:52.437 --> 14:54.047
My pleasure.
People will love it

14:54.134 --> 14:55.831
in the next Hong Kong Vogue.

14:55.918 --> 14:58.530
Thank you, Russell.

14:58.617 --> 15:01.576
Hong Kong Vogue? I knew it.
Your dress is a disaster.

15:01.663 --> 15:03.274
If you wore a Bottega gown,
like I told you to,

15:03.361 --> 15:04.623
we'd be in the American Vogue.

15:04.710 --> 15:06.668
You can wear
that gown to Hell, Eddie.

15:06.755 --> 15:08.583
Stop!

15:08.670 --> 15:09.845
Then there's Astrid.

15:09.932 --> 15:11.934
Ah. I remember Astrid.

15:12.021 --> 15:13.806
She's like who I wanna be
when I grow up.

15:13.893 --> 15:15.677
Astrid is awesome.

15:15.764 --> 15:16.765
And she's probably
the only one

15:16.852 --> 15:18.158
I'm actually close with.

15:18.245 --> 15:19.681
And she's really grounded
and down to earth,

15:19.768 --> 15:21.248
once you get to know her.

15:28.603 --> 15:31.302
Not only did she graduate
top of her class at Oxford,

15:31.389 --> 15:34.566
start multiple charities,
and is a fashion icon,

15:34.653 --> 15:37.699
Astrid has the biggest heart
of any of my cousins.

15:39.397 --> 15:41.181
Mummy? See what I made
for bunny?

15:41.268 --> 15:42.313
No, not now.

15:48.101 --> 15:51.713
Hi, I'm Astrid.
What's your name?

15:51.800 --> 15:52.932
Vita.

15:53.019 --> 15:54.412
And who's this?

15:54.977 --> 15:56.631
Bun-Bun.

15:56.718 --> 16:00.157
Well, I think Bun-Bun looks
very dashing with his bow.

16:00.244 --> 16:01.462
You have a good eye.

16:01.549 --> 16:02.855
Thank you.

16:02.942 --> 16:05.118
Miss Leong, right this way.

16:05.205 --> 16:06.511
It's very nice
to meet you both.

16:16.651 --> 16:19.132
These are all
brand-new from Antwerp.

16:19.219 --> 16:22.048
You're the first person
I've shown them to.

16:26.400 --> 16:27.532
What are those?

16:29.403 --> 16:30.883
Those?

16:33.277 --> 16:35.757
Those are very special.

16:35.844 --> 16:38.151
Burmese pearl drop earrings.

16:38.238 --> 16:42.764
Set with emeralds, and rare
pigeon blood-red rubies.

16:42.851 --> 16:45.506
They were worn
by Queen Supayalat

16:45.593 --> 16:49.206
at her self-anointed
coronation in 1878.

16:50.207 --> 16:52.905
How much?

16:52.992 --> 16:55.647
Having you wear
one of my pieces

16:55.734 --> 16:58.780
is better publicity
than I can buy.

16:58.867 --> 17:03.002
I'll let them go at cost.
1.2 million.

17:07.354 --> 17:09.356
So if you have
all this family there,

17:09.443 --> 17:11.531
why are we staying in a hotel?

17:11.618 --> 17:13.534
Aren't good Chinese sons

17:13.621 --> 17:16.363
supposed to stay
with their parents?

17:16.450 --> 17:21.063
Well, because A,
I'm not that good a son.

17:22.717 --> 17:23.675
And B,

17:26.590 --> 17:29.202
I just want you to myself,
just for a bit.

17:29.898 --> 17:30.986
That okay?

17:33.772 --> 17:35.295
Okay.

18:11.940 --> 18:15.335
God, I can't believe this
airport has a butterfly garden

18:15.422 --> 18:17.555
and a movie theater.

18:17.642 --> 18:20.732
JFK is just salmonella
and despair.

18:20.819 --> 18:23.169
Nick! Nick!

18:30.524 --> 18:31.656
Araminta!

18:34.267 --> 18:35.877
- I missed you.
- I missed you, too.

18:35.964 --> 18:37.226
- Rachel.
- Hi.

18:37.314 --> 18:38.532
There he is.

18:38.619 --> 18:40.142
It's so nice
to finally meet you.

18:40.229 --> 18:41.970
It's so nice to meet you, too.

18:42.057 --> 18:44.233
- Nicki-Nick!
- It's been too long, brother.

18:44.321 --> 18:46.758
It has been too long.
Welcome back.

18:46.845 --> 18:47.976
You guys didn't have to
pick us up.

18:48.063 --> 18:49.761
Of course we did. We had to.

18:49.848 --> 18:52.067
Of course I had to come
welcome my best man properly.

18:52.154 --> 18:53.504
- Hi, Rachel.
- Hello.

18:53.591 --> 18:55.027
Oh! Lovely to finally
meet you.

18:55.114 --> 18:56.333
Nice to meet you, too.

18:56.420 --> 18:57.290
Shall we?
Let me help you with this.

18:57.377 --> 18:58.639
Yes.

18:58.726 --> 19:00.206
- These are for you.
- I can grab these.

19:00.293 --> 19:01.555
I know
they're a bit over-the-top.

19:01.642 --> 19:03.209
Let's get
you guys localized.

19:03.296 --> 19:04.428
- Are you hungry?
- I'm always hungry.

19:04.515 --> 19:07.561
So let's eat
everything we can.

19:24.186 --> 19:28.190
Welcome to
heaven on earth!

19:28.277 --> 19:30.802
I hope you're hungry.
I am bloody starving.

19:37.939 --> 19:40.768
Guys! Here! Whoo!

19:40.855 --> 19:43.249
Come with me.

