37:29.575 --> 37:30.968
You know,
when you said you grew up

37:31.055 --> 37:32.709
in your grandma's house,

37:32.796 --> 37:35.799
I wasn't expecting this.

37:35.886 --> 37:37.453
Thank you.

37:37.540 --> 37:41.152
Oh, no, no.
Those are for your fingers.

37:41.239 --> 37:42.588
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

37:42.675 --> 37:44.590
A little bit much, I know.

37:44.677 --> 37:46.462
I mean,
this place is gorgeous.

37:46.549 --> 37:48.202
And like
the rolling green hills.

37:48.289 --> 37:51.510
I mean, there are
armed guards out there.

37:51.597 --> 37:52.990
And a giant tiger.

37:53.077 --> 37:54.731
Okay.

37:55.775 --> 37:58.517
That is Mr. Harimau.

37:58.604 --> 38:00.693
Now, my great-grandfather
actually shot him

38:00.780 --> 38:02.521
when he ran into the house.

38:02.608 --> 38:06.307
But Astrid and I, we used to
hide cigarettes in his paws.

38:06.394 --> 38:07.831
Do you wanna head in?

38:07.918 --> 38:10.050
Actually, I wanted to
bring you over

38:10.137 --> 38:11.399
- to my mum first.
- Oh.

38:11.922 --> 38:13.314
Come on.

38:54.399 --> 38:55.487
Mum.

38:58.708 --> 39:01.058
You need a haircut.
So unkempt.

39:01.145 --> 39:03.103
And you look tired
from your trip.

39:03.190 --> 39:05.932
I'm gonna ask the cook
to make you some herbal soup.

39:07.760 --> 39:09.414
I'll send it
to the hotel later.

39:09.501 --> 39:12.286
Mum, this is Rachel Chu.

39:12.373 --> 39:15.812
Oh, my gosh! I'm so happy
to meet you, Mrs. Young.

39:15.899 --> 39:18.162
Or Auntie. Right?

39:18.249 --> 39:21.295
I'm learning
the lingo.

39:21.382 --> 39:23.602
I'm very glad
to finally meet you, too.

39:23.689 --> 39:25.952
And I'm sorry Nick's father
couldn't be here.

39:26.039 --> 39:28.041
He was called to business
in Shanghai.

39:28.128 --> 39:31.305
I told Rachel when duty calls,
Dad answers.

39:31.392 --> 39:32.698
As it should be.

39:32.785 --> 39:34.526
Nick tells me
you're a professor, too.

39:34.613 --> 39:36.006
What do you teach?

39:36.093 --> 39:37.703
Um, I teach economics.

39:37.790 --> 39:40.532
And she's brilliant.
NYU's youngest faculty member.

39:44.928 --> 39:46.277
So, economics...

39:46.364 --> 39:47.713
Sounds challenging.

39:47.800 --> 39:49.672
Are your parents
academics as well?

39:49.759 --> 39:53.197
No. Well, my dad actually died
before I was born,

39:53.284 --> 39:55.373
and my mom
didn't even go to college.

39:55.460 --> 39:57.157
She actually hardly spoke
any English

39:57.244 --> 39:59.464
when she immigrated
to the United States.

39:59.551 --> 40:01.901
But she worked really hard,
and she studied,

40:01.988 --> 40:03.816
and she earned
her real estate license

40:03.903 --> 40:06.123
while she was waiting tables
to support us.

40:06.210 --> 40:07.733
Now, she likes to say

40:07.820 --> 40:10.301
that she's Flushing's
top real estate broker.

40:10.388 --> 40:16.046
Self-made woman.
She must be so proud of you.

40:16.133 --> 40:18.265
Well, she knows that I'm
passionate about what I do,

40:18.352 --> 40:19.745
and she's always
wanted that for me.

40:21.486 --> 40:25.446
Pursuing one's passion.
How American.

40:25.533 --> 40:28.101
Well, your mother's
very open-minded,

40:28.188 --> 40:29.581
not like here,

40:29.668 --> 40:31.452
where parents are obsessed

40:31.539 --> 40:33.411
with shaping the life
of their children.

40:35.631 --> 40:36.675
That's dinner.

40:36.762 --> 40:37.937
Go ahead.

40:38.024 --> 40:39.373
I'll be out in a minute.

40:39.460 --> 40:41.767
Rachel, it was lovely
meeting you.

40:41.854 --> 40:45.118
Thank you. You, too.

40:45.205 --> 40:46.859
Okay, she hates me.

40:46.946 --> 40:48.731
She takes a little minute
to warm up,

40:48.818 --> 40:50.733
- but we'll get there.
- A minute?

41:04.224 --> 41:06.487
- Nicki! Rachel!
- Astrid.

41:07.488 --> 41:09.229
Hey. Good to see you.

41:09.316 --> 41:10.404
I'm so glad you could make it.

41:10.491 --> 41:12.015
- Michael.
- Nick.

41:12.102 --> 41:13.407
Astrid. So good
to see a face I know.

41:13.494 --> 41:14.931
This is my husband, Michael.

41:15.018 --> 41:17.194
Nice to meet you.
Heard so much about you.

41:17.281 --> 41:18.674
Nice to meet you, Michael.

41:18.761 --> 41:21.546
Hey, the golden boy's back!
Nick!

41:21.633 --> 41:23.896
And you must be Rachel.

41:23.983 --> 41:25.942
I'm Edison Cheng.
This is my wife.

41:26.029 --> 41:27.508
- Hi. I'm...
- Her name is Fiona.

41:27.595 --> 41:29.249
So I see you've already met
Princess Astrid

41:29.336 --> 41:31.774
and her little
soldier toy-boy, Mikey.

41:31.861 --> 41:33.776
You know, Mikey is a big-shot
tech startup guy.

41:33.863 --> 41:35.299
So if you forget
your password,

41:35.386 --> 41:36.996
he's your man.

41:37.083 --> 41:40.347
So you're from the Taiwan
plastic Chus, right?

41:40.434 --> 41:43.046
Can I punch him in the face?
Just once.

41:43.133 --> 41:44.395
Take a number.

41:44.482 --> 41:47.354
I'll be in my usual corner.
Champagne?

41:47.441 --> 41:48.878
Thank you.

41:53.404 --> 41:56.886
So, have you prepped Rachel
to face the wolves?

41:56.973 --> 41:58.757
Rachel is a New Yorker.

41:58.844 --> 42:01.455
She lectures millennials
for a living.

42:01.542 --> 42:03.544
I think she'll manage
our family.

42:03.631 --> 42:05.808
You've been away too long.

42:05.895 --> 42:07.418
Okay, sorry, time out.

42:07.505 --> 42:09.333
So you're not
from a Taiwan Chu family?

42:09.420 --> 42:10.769
Nope.

42:10.856 --> 42:12.205
Hong Kong telecom Chus?

42:12.292 --> 42:13.424
No.

42:13.511 --> 42:15.382
Malaysian packing peanut Chus?

42:15.469 --> 42:16.993
Is that really a thing?

42:17.080 --> 42:18.908
- Yeah, it's everywhere.
- I'm gonna stop you there

42:18.995 --> 42:20.518
because I'm gonna take her
on the rounds.

42:20.605 --> 42:22.520
- We'll be back, though.
- No, wait. Hang on.

42:22.607 --> 42:25.523
China instant noodle Chus.
Rachel,

42:25.610 --> 42:28.091
Chu are you?

42:29.353 --> 42:31.398
Ugh. Let's go.

42:34.662 --> 42:37.013
This is Auntie Alix
and Auntie Felicity.

42:37.100 --> 42:39.102
Hi!
It's so nice to meet you.

42:39.189 --> 42:41.931
I've never been
to a tan huaparty before.

42:42.018 --> 42:44.020
We love any excuse
to throw a soiree.

42:44.107 --> 42:46.152
Do your parents like
to entertain?

42:46.239 --> 42:48.938
Oh. I'm sorry.
Your mother's single.

42:49.677 --> 42:51.114
Yup.

42:51.201 --> 42:52.506
Auntie Jacqueline.

42:52.593 --> 42:54.030
One of my parents'
oldest friends.

42:54.117 --> 42:57.120
I actually met Nick's father
at Cambridge.

42:57.207 --> 43:00.036
So, what line of work
is your father in?

43:00.123 --> 43:02.299
Oh, my father died
before I was born.

43:02.386 --> 43:05.258
But he was a factory worker
in China.

43:20.534 --> 43:22.319
This is Ling Cheh,

43:22.406 --> 43:24.147
my old nanny.

43:28.542 --> 43:32.242
Look, now's the time
we need all hands on deck.

43:32.329 --> 43:34.461
Please, please,
just do me this favor.

43:34.548 --> 43:35.941
Thank you. Bye-bye.

43:37.595 --> 43:39.727
They started
clearing away dinner.

43:39.815 --> 43:41.338
Your favorites.

43:42.730 --> 43:44.558
Thank you.

43:46.996 --> 43:48.824
You know if you need
bodies at the office,

43:48.911 --> 43:50.303
I could always come in
and help out.

43:52.436 --> 43:54.481
The glamorous Astrid Leong

43:54.568 --> 43:58.137
- working as an assistant?
- Mmm-hmm.

43:58.224 --> 44:02.707
Wait, isn't Araminta's
bachelorette party tomorrow?

44:02.794 --> 44:06.102
And this will be the perfect
excuse to get out of it.

44:06.189 --> 44:08.582
Thank you. Really.

44:08.669 --> 44:10.410
But I've got
everything covered.

44:11.585 --> 44:12.848
Okay.

44:14.066 --> 44:15.589
I forgot to get you a fork.

44:15.676 --> 44:17.504
It's okay, you stay.
I'll go get it.

44:26.600 --> 44:29.299
Michael,
I think it's the office.

44:45.184 --> 44:48.187
Oh, my God! Nick, I can't
believe I just did that.

44:48.274 --> 44:49.972
It's fine. I don't think
anybody even noticed.

44:50.059 --> 44:51.538
I think I freaked out
your nanny...

44:51.625 --> 44:53.845
Oh, my God!

44:53.932 --> 44:55.281
So sorry.

44:55.368 --> 44:56.326
It's fine,
don't worry about it.

44:56.413 --> 44:57.849
Can I have a tissue please?

44:57.936 --> 45:00.373
Go, go. Get changed.
I'll keep Rachel company.

45:00.460 --> 45:02.375
Thank you, Oli.
You're in good hands.

45:02.462 --> 45:03.550
Give me two minutes.
I'll change.

45:03.637 --> 45:05.030
Sorry.

45:06.902 --> 45:08.120
Hi, I'm Rachel.

45:08.207 --> 45:09.643
Oh, I know.

45:09.730 --> 45:11.950
Rachel! Rachel!

45:12.037 --> 45:13.647
I heard you thought
Ah Mawas the cook!

45:15.127 --> 45:16.737
Ahh!

45:16.824 --> 45:19.392
On the bright side,
you're the talk of the party.

45:19.479 --> 45:20.828
People like your dress.

45:20.916 --> 45:21.960
Oh, I did that.

45:22.047 --> 45:23.222
- Oh.
- I know!

45:23.309 --> 45:25.094
Such a chic '70s goddess.

45:25.181 --> 45:26.660
I know.

45:26.747 --> 45:28.619
It's very disco Cleopatra,
but in a good way.

45:28.706 --> 45:30.012
That's exactly
what I was going for.

45:30.099 --> 45:32.840
Oh, well. Oliver.

45:32.928 --> 45:34.407
- Hi.
- I like your shoes.

45:34.494 --> 45:36.061
Oh, thank you.
I'm Peik Lin. Ditto.

45:36.148 --> 45:37.584
- Cheers.
- There you go.

45:37.671 --> 45:38.890
Gosh, these are lovely.

45:38.977 --> 45:39.978
They're clip-ons. Thank you.

45:40.065 --> 45:41.806
Are they? Oh, wow!

45:41.893 --> 45:43.808
So, Oliver,
are you a cousin, too?

45:43.895 --> 45:47.072
Mmm. Well, I'm one of
the poorer relations.

45:47.159 --> 45:48.595
The rainbow sheep
of the family.

45:49.857 --> 45:51.163
But I make myself useful.

45:51.250 --> 45:53.296
Whatever the Youngs want,
I procure.

45:53.383 --> 45:56.299
Golden koi fish,
Huanghuali furniture.

45:56.386 --> 45:57.996
A rare Cambodian gong.

45:58.083 --> 46:00.738
Why would they want to buy
a rare Cambodian gong?

46:03.871 --> 46:05.438
Because they can.

46:10.574 --> 46:13.011
Ah Mainsists
all your clothes be washed

46:13.098 --> 46:14.839
and pressed every two weeks.

46:17.059 --> 46:19.148
This one.

46:19.235 --> 46:22.020
Everything is exactly
as I left it.

46:30.463 --> 46:32.378
Looking for your cigars?

46:32.465 --> 46:34.859
I had them thrown out
years ago.

46:37.644 --> 46:39.255
Never could get
anything past you, could I?

46:41.170 --> 46:43.955
I keep telling Ah Ma
to put your things away,

46:44.042 --> 46:45.391
but she says this room

46:45.478 --> 46:47.219
makes her feel
like you're still here.

46:49.613 --> 46:51.615
Well, I got an earful

46:51.702 --> 46:54.096
when you didn't move back
last year.

46:55.619 --> 46:58.317
Your father and I were really

46:58.404 --> 47:00.058
looking forward
to having you home.

47:03.322 --> 47:05.020
He's not getting any younger.

47:05.890 --> 47:07.283
With you on board,

47:07.370 --> 47:09.372
maybe he'll take a day off
once in a while.

47:10.895 --> 47:12.810
I know, Mum.

47:12.897 --> 47:15.421
I'm just not ready yet.

47:15.508 --> 47:17.641
There's things in New York
that I wanna see through.

47:20.557 --> 47:24.126
Well, I'm happy
I finally met Rachel.

47:24.213 --> 47:26.432
She is very impressive.

47:26.519 --> 47:28.608
I think so, too.

47:28.695 --> 47:29.957
I thought
you might be excited

47:30.045 --> 47:32.264
that the first girl
that I bring home

47:32.351 --> 47:34.310
is a Chinese professor.

47:35.746 --> 47:38.053
Chinese American.

47:41.665 --> 47:45.190
You know, bringing her home,

47:45.277 --> 47:48.106
introducing her
at a large family gathering,

47:49.151 --> 47:50.848
some people may say...

47:50.935 --> 47:53.111
When there's something
to say

47:53.198 --> 47:56.506
about Rachel and me,
you'll be first to hear.

47:59.683 --> 48:04.992
But some things I need to
figure out on my own.

48:05.080 --> 48:07.865
Is that an American accent
I'm hearing?

48:09.736 --> 48:10.911
How do I look?

48:18.528 --> 48:19.790
Perfect.

48:33.543 --> 48:35.588
Everyone! Everyone!

48:35.675 --> 48:38.591
The tan huaplants
very rarely bloom,

48:38.678 --> 48:41.159
and even then only at night.

48:41.246 --> 48:45.598
Their beauty is spectacular
but fleeting.

48:45.685 --> 48:48.558
By dawn, they'll be gone.

48:48.645 --> 48:50.603
Come. Come.

48:59.438 --> 49:02.093
Oh, someone forgot
to wear a bra.

49:02.180 --> 49:06.967
Kitty Pong. Cousin Alistair's
latest flame. An actress.

49:07.054 --> 49:11.624
Rumor is, she was in a porno. Two Girls, One Cup of Noodles.

49:11.711 --> 49:14.236
You know, I thought I would
like that more than I did.

49:14.323 --> 49:16.020
- The book was much better.
- Mmm-hmm.

49:18.762 --> 49:22.809
Is it just me
or are people staring at me?

49:22.896 --> 49:26.726
Oh, they're just jealous.
You nabbed the crown prince.

49:26.813 --> 49:30.165
Nicki is Ah Ma'sfavorite,
in line to inherit everything.

49:30.252 --> 49:32.950
No surprise there
when that's the competition.

49:35.126 --> 49:36.954
Oh, speaking of
the grande dame...

49:59.019 --> 50:00.195
There you are.

50:00.282 --> 50:01.413
I've been looking
all over for you.

50:01.500 --> 50:03.763
You ready to meet
my grandmother?

50:06.201 --> 50:07.202
Ah Ma...

50:49.853 --> 50:52.159
Look,
they're in full bloom.

51:08.872 --> 51:11.614
It's so nice
having Nick back home.

51:11.701 --> 51:14.051
But he seems different.

51:16.401 --> 51:19.535
When children are away
from home too long,

51:19.622 --> 51:21.363
they forget who they are.

51:31.764 --> 51:33.940
What's up? Let's jam!

51:41.208 --> 51:45.517
Rachel!
So happy you're here. Oh!

51:45.604 --> 51:49.391
Oh, my God.
Your Gap look, brilliant.

51:49.478 --> 51:51.436
Thanks.

51:51.523 --> 51:53.656
- She's coming with me.
- Uh, hold on.

51:53.743 --> 51:55.658
Kiss. 36 hours. Bye.

51:55.745 --> 51:57.964
- Minty, one piece please.
- Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

51:58.051 --> 51:59.531
Not listening at all.

51:59.618 --> 52:02.229
So, I'm gonna intro you
to my posse.

52:02.317 --> 52:05.189
We're flying to
my mom's resort in Sumatra.

52:05.276 --> 52:09.106
She's closed down
the whole place just for us.

52:09.193 --> 52:11.021
We're gonna have so much fun.

52:11.108 --> 52:13.980
Come on, meet the girls.
Girls, this is Rachel Chu.

52:14.067 --> 52:15.068
Hi!

52:20.509 --> 52:22.598
So you let Bernard Tai
organize all of this?

52:22.685 --> 52:23.686
Yeah.

52:24.774 --> 52:25.818
Bernard.

52:25.905 --> 52:26.993
Hey.

52:27.994 --> 52:30.301
This is for you, asshole.

52:33.870 --> 52:38.614
Tina! Tini!
The twins are in the house!

52:38.701 --> 52:42.618
I'm so glad you made it!
How are you?

52:42.705 --> 52:44.315
It's easy to make
a killer entrance

52:44.402 --> 52:46.230
when you come
as a matching set.

52:46.317 --> 52:49.189
Hi, we haven't met.
I'm Amanda Ling.

52:49.276 --> 52:51.496
Hi, I'm Rachel Chu.

52:51.583 --> 52:53.498
Oh, you're
Nick Young's friend.

52:53.585 --> 52:55.935
- Yeah.
- Word gets around fast here.

52:56.022 --> 52:58.329
You're a professor
at NYU, right?

52:58.416 --> 53:00.636
Yes. Um, what about you?

53:00.723 --> 53:02.855
Oh, I'm a lawyer.
General counsel

53:02.942 --> 53:04.988
to the Young Family
Corporation, actually.

53:05.075 --> 53:06.598
That's very impressive.

53:06.685 --> 53:09.427
Mmm. Nah. Just good,
old-fashioned nepotism.

53:09.514 --> 53:12.343
I grew up with Nick and Colin.
We're family friends.

53:12.430 --> 53:14.214
It's nice to meet you,
Rachel Chu.

53:15.955 --> 53:19.742
Ladies, come on.
We're wheels up in five.

53:19.829 --> 53:20.830
Let's do this?

53:20.917 --> 53:22.222
Let's go.

53:28.533 --> 53:30.796
Yeah!

53:30.883 --> 53:34.017
All I wanted was a weekend
away with my boys.

53:34.104 --> 53:36.628
And some beer.
Maybe some rugby.

53:36.715 --> 53:38.978
Don't worry. It's gonna be
great, whatever happens.

53:39.065 --> 53:40.327
Yeah.

53:40.415 --> 53:42.199
Let's make
some babies!

53:42.286 --> 53:45.158
I don't think it will be.

53:56.213 --> 53:58.955
Any asshole can plan
a normal stag party.

53:59.042 --> 54:02.306
Hookers, drugs, dog-fighting.

54:02.393 --> 54:05.048
That's minor league shit.

54:05.135 --> 54:07.398
To organize a party
this massive...

54:07.485 --> 54:09.487
Takes a massive asshole.

54:09.574 --> 54:12.229
...takes a goddamn mastermind.

54:12.316 --> 54:14.100
Where exactly is this party?

54:15.841 --> 54:17.103
It's right there.

54:21.717 --> 54:22.979
Bloody hell!

54:33.903 --> 54:34.947
Whoo!

55:05.369 --> 55:07.023
Did you just see that?

55:07.110 --> 55:08.894
Oh, my God, Nick.
What are you worried about?

55:08.981 --> 55:10.200
You don't have to
keep Rachel happy.

55:10.287 --> 55:11.636
She's just lucky to be here.

55:11.723 --> 55:13.116
Nice, Eddie.

55:13.203 --> 55:14.813
Oh, what?

55:14.900 --> 55:16.598
So we're gonna pretend
like that's not the truth?

55:16.685 --> 55:17.816
Are we in some kind of
fairy tale story

55:17.903 --> 55:19.122
that I don't know about?

55:19.209 --> 55:20.384
Did you find a shoe
at midnight

55:20.471 --> 55:21.951
and jump in a pumpkin?

55:22.038 --> 55:24.214
Yo, I got so much shit
about marrying Fiona,

55:24.301 --> 55:25.781
and her parents own

55:25.868 --> 55:27.870
the biggest shipping company
in Hong Kong.

55:27.957 --> 55:30.176
Hey, Araminta's adorable,
but you think your dad

55:30.263 --> 55:31.917
would be spending millions
on this wedding

55:32.004 --> 55:35.007
if her parents didn't own
a billion-dollar resort chain?

55:35.094 --> 55:37.183
What's Rachel bringing
to the table?

55:37.270 --> 55:39.664
Oh! Small tits!

55:39.751 --> 55:41.187
Oh!

55:41.274 --> 55:44.147
Hey. It's not worth it, man.
They're drunk.

55:44.234 --> 55:47.977
Hey, guys,
this is boring. Massage time.

55:48.064 --> 55:50.806
And you, the bachelor,

55:50.893 --> 55:53.504
you're gonna get one
before this weekend is over.

55:53.591 --> 55:57.116
Or we're gonna tie you up
and shave your coo coo chara.

55:58.770 --> 56:00.424
Coo coo chara!

56:00.511 --> 56:02.557
Hey, come try this.

56:03.949 --> 56:05.734
We have to get off this ship.

56:17.136 --> 56:20.096
Welcome to paradise.

56:20.183 --> 56:23.447
This is Samsara Island.

56:25.797 --> 56:28.408
This weekend
is about sisterhood

56:28.495 --> 56:32.761
and connecting
with the divine in all of us.

56:32.848 --> 56:36.852
So, I hope you'll all find
your bliss,

56:36.939 --> 56:40.812
starting with an all-paid
shopping spree

56:40.899 --> 56:42.901
at the fashion boutique!

56:48.341 --> 56:51.083
Come on! Come on!

56:53.956 --> 56:55.305
Bitch, I saw this first!

56:55.392 --> 56:56.567
But you have ping pong tits!

56:56.654 --> 56:57.655
What about
your mosquito bites?

56:57.742 --> 56:59.526
- No!
- You know it's true!

56:59.614 --> 57:03.922
One more minute!
You keep what you can carry.

57:04.009 --> 57:08.884
One more minute!
You keep what you can carry.

57:08.971 --> 57:12.888
Yeah, no one loves free stuff
more than rich people.

57:12.975 --> 57:14.846
Just the one dress for you?

57:14.933 --> 57:17.327
I don't wanna lose an arm.

57:17.414 --> 57:20.069
Ooh. Well, in that case,

57:23.507 --> 57:25.074
one last touch.

57:33.256 --> 57:35.127
Well, isn't Nick a lucky guy.

57:35.214 --> 57:36.433
Time's up!

57:36.520 --> 57:39.088
Next stop... Spa!

57:46.095 --> 57:48.010
You're a genius.
You know that, right?

57:48.097 --> 57:49.620
What's a best man for?

57:49.707 --> 57:51.840
Guess that pilot's license
came in handy after all.

57:51.927 --> 57:53.537
Here you go, champ.

57:53.624 --> 57:55.234
Oh, thank you, sir.

57:55.321 --> 57:57.715
Mmm. I think that is the best
beer I've ever had.

57:57.802 --> 58:00.370
I'm gonna have to agree
with you on that.

58:03.808 --> 58:05.201
You know,
if it wasn't for Araminta,

58:05.288 --> 58:06.855
I'd ask you to marry me.

58:09.335 --> 58:10.510
Although,

58:12.904 --> 58:14.166
there is a little something

58:14.253 --> 58:15.385
that might get
in the way of that.

58:18.518 --> 58:20.129
Mmm.

58:20.216 --> 58:22.522
- No!
- Yeah.

58:22.609 --> 58:24.829
- Is that real?
- Yes.

58:24.916 --> 58:26.483
- Wow! Yes!
- Yes.

58:26.570 --> 58:28.485
Yes, man! Congratulations!

58:28.572 --> 58:30.617
- I know.
- That is freaking amazing.

58:30.705 --> 58:32.184
- I'm ready.
- You're ready.

58:32.271 --> 58:34.230
You're doing it.

58:34.317 --> 58:36.275
Nick, I'm really happy
for you, man.

58:36.362 --> 58:38.190
Thanks, dude.

58:47.417 --> 58:49.680
I think my masseuse
just got me pregnant.

58:55.338 --> 58:58.210
I can see why Nick put off
coming back to Singapore.

58:58.994 --> 59:00.647
What do you mean?

59:00.735 --> 59:03.650
You know, he was supposed
to come back last year,

59:03.738 --> 59:06.001
take over the family business.

59:06.088 --> 59:08.481
His parents freaked out
when he didn't.

59:08.568 --> 59:12.921
But, now that he's back,
I'm sure all is forgiven.

59:13.008 --> 59:14.836
But he's not back
for good.

59:14.923 --> 59:16.663
I mean,
we're just here for a wedding.

59:20.798 --> 59:22.278
Wow!

59:23.932 --> 59:24.976
But?

59:25.063 --> 59:27.370
No, I'm really happy for you.

59:27.457 --> 59:29.459
Colin, I've known you
since you were in nappies.

59:29.546 --> 59:31.853
I know when there's something
on your mind.

59:31.940 --> 59:34.769
Well, it wasn't
that long ago

59:34.856 --> 59:38.076
that you were sure
you were moving back home.

59:38.163 --> 59:41.950
And I mean, Rachel loves
her job in New York.

59:43.212 --> 59:45.867
Yeah, we're gonna
figure that out.

59:45.954 --> 59:49.044
You're going to
figure it out. Right.

59:49.131 --> 59:51.829
Rachel, I get it.

59:51.916 --> 59:53.222
It's hard knowing
where you stand

59:53.309 --> 59:55.137
with someone
like Nicholas Young.

59:55.224 --> 59:57.704
He has all that pressure
from his family.

59:57.792 --> 01:00:01.708
Not just in business,
but in who he's dating.

01:00:01.796 --> 01:00:03.928
It's like, you just never know

01:00:04.015 --> 01:00:06.583
what's quite going on
in that gorgeous head of his.

01:00:09.978 --> 01:00:12.937
Nick told you that
we were together, right?

01:00:13.024 --> 01:00:15.505
It's ancient history now.

01:00:15.592 --> 01:00:18.900
Although our families,
particularly his mother,

01:00:18.987 --> 01:00:22.207
always wanted us
to get married.

01:00:22.294 --> 01:00:23.861
I guess we weren't ready then.

01:00:23.948 --> 01:00:26.516
Dude, ever since
primary school,

01:00:26.603 --> 01:00:28.344
you were always going to be

01:00:28.431 --> 01:00:30.868
the next chairman
of the Young Corporation,

01:00:30.955 --> 01:00:33.044
your family's shining heir.

01:00:33.131 --> 01:00:34.480
You really think
your family's going to

01:00:34.567 --> 01:00:36.831
accept anything
less than that?

01:00:36.918 --> 01:00:38.441
I mean, unless you...

01:00:39.659 --> 01:00:40.791
No.

01:00:42.227 --> 01:00:44.664
Are you thinking
of walking out?

01:00:44.751 --> 01:00:47.319
Leaving everything
to bloody Alistair and Eddie?

01:00:47.406 --> 01:00:49.452
I'm not walking out
on anything.

01:00:49.539 --> 01:00:52.934
I met a girl, I fell in love
and I want to marry her.

01:00:53.021 --> 01:00:55.414
And it can't just be
one thing or the other.

01:00:55.501 --> 01:00:57.112
Uh... No, no, no.

01:00:57.199 --> 01:01:00.463
It's not that simple.
You know that.

01:01:00.550 --> 01:01:02.552
I really admire you.

01:01:02.639 --> 01:01:05.816
It takes guts
coming all the way over here,

01:01:05.903 --> 01:01:07.774
facing Nick's family.

01:01:07.862 --> 01:01:12.170
Especially when Eleanor isn't
exactly in your corner.

01:01:12.257 --> 01:01:14.564
Okay, your family aside,
have you ever thought about

01:01:14.651 --> 01:01:16.914
what your relationship
with Rachel

01:01:17.001 --> 01:01:19.351
will be like
if you got married?

01:01:19.438 --> 01:01:20.875
I mean, okay,

01:01:20.962 --> 01:01:22.920
you're Nicholas Young.
You're untouchable.

01:01:23.007 --> 01:01:27.794
You always have been.
But Rachel's not.

01:01:27.882 --> 01:01:30.972
And if she becomes
Mrs. Nicholas Young,

01:01:31.059 --> 01:01:33.278
every day for her
is going to be a struggle.

01:01:38.675 --> 01:01:42.722
I heard she told Tini
that Nick is a good catch.

01:01:42.809 --> 01:01:45.595
So typical.
She's not even that pretty.

01:01:45.682 --> 01:01:48.815
It's like she's never heard
of plastic surgery.

01:01:48.903 --> 01:01:50.382
Oh, shit.

01:01:56.736 --> 01:01:58.173
Sorry.

01:01:58.260 --> 01:01:59.826
You sure she's ready for that?

01:02:08.574 --> 01:02:09.836
Rachel?

01:02:17.714 --> 01:02:19.890
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

01:02:19.977 --> 01:02:22.240
Let's just forget
about those girls.

01:02:22.327 --> 01:02:23.459
Camp out here

01:02:23.546 --> 01:02:24.590
and order room service?

01:02:36.341 --> 01:02:37.429
I'll call security.

01:02:37.516 --> 01:02:38.604
No.

01:02:40.911 --> 01:02:44.306
I'm not gonna make a scene.

01:02:44.393 --> 01:02:46.699
I'm not gonna give them
the satisfaction.

01:02:52.749 --> 01:02:56.187
This weekend was supposed
to be mani-pedis,

01:02:56.274 --> 01:02:58.668
cocktails served
in pineapples.

01:02:58.755 --> 01:03:01.149
This definitely wasn't
on the menu.

01:03:01.236 --> 01:03:04.021
Why would Araminta even have
friends like that?

01:03:04.108 --> 01:03:05.892
They're so mean.

01:03:05.980 --> 01:03:08.112
Well, you grow up
your whole lives together,

01:03:08.199 --> 01:03:09.809
you make excuses for people.

01:03:10.985 --> 01:03:13.074
Specially the morons.

01:03:13.161 --> 01:03:15.554
I mean, I know Michael didn't
have to deal with catty,

01:03:15.641 --> 01:03:18.644
fish-killing sociopaths.

01:03:18.731 --> 01:03:20.995
How did you two
get through all this?

01:03:22.909 --> 01:03:27.218
Well, I didn't have it quite
as bad, but it wasn't pretty.

01:03:29.090 --> 01:03:32.093
Well, at least tell me
it gets better.

01:03:32.180 --> 01:03:34.312
Of course it does.

01:03:38.882 --> 01:03:39.883
You okay?

01:03:41.363 --> 01:03:42.538
Yeah.

01:03:56.856 --> 01:04:00.817
Actually... No.

01:04:06.866 --> 01:04:08.477
You could talk to me.

01:04:16.267 --> 01:04:19.140
Michael is having an affair.

01:04:28.062 --> 01:04:30.107
I'm really sorry, Astrid.

01:05:00.181 --> 01:05:02.400
I thought I was here
to meet your family,

01:05:02.487 --> 01:05:04.663
go to your best friend's
wedding, eat some good food.

01:05:04.750 --> 01:05:07.536
Instead, I feel like I'm
a villain in a soap opera

01:05:07.623 --> 01:05:10.626
who's plotting to steal
your family fortune.

01:05:11.801 --> 01:05:13.542
What happened?

01:05:14.630 --> 01:05:16.153
I mean, I met Amanda.

01:05:16.240 --> 01:05:18.068
She told me
that everyone here thinks

01:05:18.155 --> 01:05:19.330
that I'm the evil person

01:05:19.417 --> 01:05:20.810
that prevented you
from moving back

01:05:20.897 --> 01:05:21.985
to Singapore last year,

01:05:22.072 --> 01:05:23.247
when I didn't even know

01:05:23.334 --> 01:05:25.467
you were supposed
to come home.

01:05:25.554 --> 01:05:27.556
You have every reason
to be upset.

01:05:27.643 --> 01:05:29.166
I'm not done yet.

01:05:29.253 --> 01:05:33.170
There was also this gutted,
bloody fish

01:05:33.257 --> 01:05:35.172
that Araminta's friends
left for me

01:05:35.259 --> 01:05:36.565
in my hotel room

01:05:36.652 --> 01:05:38.436
on my bed next to the words,

01:05:38.523 --> 01:05:41.483
"Catch this,
you gold-digging bitch."

01:05:41.570 --> 01:05:44.529
Written in big,
fat serial-killer letters.

01:05:44.616 --> 01:05:46.879
Is that all that happened?

01:05:46.966 --> 01:05:48.968
I mean, please tell me
that's all that happened.

01:05:49.055 --> 01:05:50.361
You know what?
I don't even care

01:05:50.448 --> 01:05:51.710
about those stupid girls

01:05:51.797 --> 01:05:53.538
with their stupid little
designer handbags

01:05:53.625 --> 01:05:54.931
and sunglasses.
I don't care about that.

01:05:55.018 --> 01:05:56.280
I don't care
that your ex-girlfriend

01:05:56.367 --> 01:05:57.716
told me all this crap.

01:05:57.803 --> 01:05:58.978
It's that you didn't
tell me any of it.

01:05:59.849 --> 01:06:01.111
I screwed up.

01:06:01.198 --> 01:06:02.243
Why? Were you trying
to test me?

01:06:02.330 --> 01:06:03.679
I really
messed up, okay?

01:06:03.766 --> 01:06:05.550
- Why would you do that?
- I made a mistake.

01:06:05.637 --> 01:06:09.119
When we first met,
you had no idea who I was,

01:06:09.206 --> 01:06:11.165
who my family were.
You didn't care!

01:06:11.252 --> 01:06:13.732
Yeah, I don't care
about that stupid stuff.

01:06:13.819 --> 01:06:16.344
Well, exactly.

01:06:16.431 --> 01:06:18.998
You are so different
from all of the women

01:06:19.085 --> 01:06:20.522
that I grew up with.

01:06:22.263 --> 01:06:24.526
And I love who I am
around you.

01:06:26.310 --> 01:06:29.487
I don't want that to change.

01:06:29.574 --> 01:06:33.404
- And that's selfish, I know.
- Mmm-hmm.

01:06:33.491 --> 01:06:35.363
I'm sorry that you had to deal
with that on your own.

01:06:38.453 --> 01:06:40.933
But I'm here now.

01:06:41.020 --> 01:06:43.284
Whatever happens,
we'll get through it together.

01:06:43.371 --> 01:06:45.155
Dead fish and all.

01:06:46.461 --> 01:06:47.984
All right?

01:06:48.071 --> 01:06:49.333
It was so gross.

01:06:50.813 --> 01:06:52.118
But I buried it.

01:06:55.165 --> 01:06:56.471
You dealt with it.

01:06:58.212 --> 01:06:59.604
Come here.

01:07:03.826 --> 01:07:05.523
You know what? We need to do
something tonight.

01:07:05.610 --> 01:07:07.395
We need to do something
that's just you and me, okay?

01:07:07.482 --> 01:07:09.397
- 100% agree.
- Yes.

01:07:09.484 --> 01:07:13.618
But we do have to go
make some dumplings first.

01:07:14.706 --> 01:07:15.794
Okay?

01:07:15.881 --> 01:07:17.100
And can we eat them?

01:07:17.187 --> 01:07:18.319
We can eat
as many as you like.

01:07:18.406 --> 01:07:19.668
Okay, fine.

01:07:46.390 --> 01:07:47.913
This is too much.

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:50.046
We're hosting
a rehearsal dinner,

01:07:50.133 --> 01:07:52.396
not feeding an army.

01:07:52.483 --> 01:07:54.703
Better too many than have
people say we're stingy.

01:07:55.878 --> 01:07:58.141
So, right.

01:07:58.228 --> 01:08:01.100
You put the baby in bed.

01:08:01.187 --> 01:08:06.323
You tuck, tuck, tuck.
Same on the other side.

01:08:06.410 --> 01:08:08.456
You give him
a kiss good night.

01:08:08.543 --> 01:08:10.284
That's so cute.

01:08:10.371 --> 01:08:12.111
- How's that?
- And then you eat the baby.

01:08:12.198 --> 01:08:14.418
Then you eat the baby
after he's cooked.

01:08:14.505 --> 01:08:16.072
No, you gotta
make sure he's cooked.

01:08:16.158 --> 01:08:17.160
Did your Ah Mateach you that?

01:08:17.247 --> 01:08:19.162
She did.

01:08:19.249 --> 01:08:20.642
I, on the other hand,

01:08:20.729 --> 01:08:22.252
was taught
by Grand-Auntie Mabel.

01:08:22.339 --> 01:08:24.645
You put the Botox in the face,

01:08:24.733 --> 01:08:28.084
and then
you pinch, pinch, pinch.

01:08:28.171 --> 01:08:30.738
Then, voila!

01:08:30.826 --> 01:08:32.828
Did you guys all learn
when you were kids?

01:08:32.915 --> 01:08:34.176
We didn't have a choice.

01:08:34.264 --> 01:08:35.874
We taught you so you'd know

01:08:35.961 --> 01:08:37.788
the blood, sweat,
and tears it took

01:08:37.876 --> 01:08:39.529
to raise and feed you monkeys.

01:08:39.617 --> 01:08:41.053
Not like the ang-mohs

01:08:41.140 --> 01:08:42.925
microwaving macaroni
and cheese

01:08:43.011 --> 01:08:44.229
for their own children.

01:08:44.318 --> 01:08:46.015
No wonder
they put their parents

01:08:46.102 --> 01:08:47.799
in the old folks' home
when they all grow up.

01:08:47.886 --> 01:08:49.714
I know!

01:08:49.801 --> 01:08:52.412
Ah Masays if we don't pass
traditions down like this,

01:08:52.500 --> 01:08:54.415
they'll disappear.

01:08:54.502 --> 01:08:56.546
God forbid, we lose
the ancient Chinese tradition

01:08:56.634 --> 01:08:57.983
of guilting your children.

01:08:59.462 --> 01:09:00.856
It's totally worth it.

01:09:00.943 --> 01:09:02.423
Mother used to wait for me
after school

01:09:02.510 --> 01:09:04.425
with a nice basket of these.

01:09:08.951 --> 01:09:11.562
Hey, I never got
after-school dumplings.

01:09:11.649 --> 01:09:13.042
Well, that's because
Auntie Felicity

01:09:13.129 --> 01:09:15.174
was doing after-school
microdermabrasion.

01:09:23.835 --> 01:09:26.621
Auntie, this is Dolce.

01:09:26.707 --> 01:09:28.404
You speak Cantonese?

01:09:28.492 --> 01:09:30.363
No, I don't.

01:09:30.451 --> 01:09:33.715
It's just great seeing
you guys all like this.

01:09:33.801 --> 01:09:35.281
When I was growing up,

01:09:35.368 --> 01:09:38.154
it was just me and my mom,
which I loved.

01:09:38.241 --> 01:09:40.895
But we didn't really have
a big family like this.

01:09:40.983 --> 01:09:42.854
It's really nice.

01:09:42.941 --> 01:09:45.203
Oh, that's so lovely
of you to say, Rachel.

01:09:45.291 --> 01:09:47.468
We are all very lucky
to have each other.

01:09:49.731 --> 01:09:52.777
That's a beautiful ring,
Auntie Eleanor.

01:09:52.863 --> 01:09:55.301
I've never seen
anything like it.

01:09:55.389 --> 01:09:58.435
Nick's father had it made
when he proposed to me.

01:09:58.522 --> 01:10:02.483
That's very romantic.
How did you guys meet?

01:10:02.570 --> 01:10:04.528
Actually, they met
at Cambridge.

01:10:04.615 --> 01:10:06.182
They were both
studying law together.

01:10:06.269 --> 01:10:07.662
Oh, I didn't know
you were a lawyer.

01:10:07.749 --> 01:10:09.620
I wasn't.
I withdrew from university

01:10:09.707 --> 01:10:10.882
when we got married.

01:10:10.969 --> 01:10:12.406
Oh.

01:10:12.493 --> 01:10:14.277
I chose to help my husband
run a business

01:10:14.364 --> 01:10:16.018
and to raise a family.

01:10:16.105 --> 01:10:18.803
For me, it was a privilege.

01:10:18.890 --> 01:10:20.979
But for you, you may think
it's old-fashioned.

01:10:22.503 --> 01:10:25.070
It's nice
you appreciate this house

01:10:25.157 --> 01:10:27.769
and us being here together
wrapping dumplings.

01:10:27.856 --> 01:10:30.598
But all this
doesn't just happen.

01:10:30.685 --> 01:10:33.209
It's because we know
to put family first,

01:10:33.296 --> 01:10:35.733
instead of chasing
one's passion.

01:10:42.740 --> 01:10:44.002
Ah Ma...

01:10:45.482 --> 01:10:46.570
Thank you.

01:10:46.657 --> 01:10:48.093
Oh, Nick.

01:10:48.180 --> 01:10:49.443
Come and sit.

01:11:03.718 --> 01:11:05.502
Mmm.

01:11:06.068 --> 01:11:07.461
Mmm.

01:11:50.025 --> 01:11:53.245
Oh, hi.
I think I'm a little lost.

01:11:53.332 --> 01:11:54.725
This house is pretty big.

01:11:58.076 --> 01:12:00.078
I'm glad I found you.

01:12:00.165 --> 01:12:02.559
I am afraid
that I've been unfair.

01:12:02.646 --> 01:12:04.039
Oh, no, you know what?

01:12:04.126 --> 01:12:05.910
I'm sorry
I made an assumption.

01:12:05.997 --> 01:12:07.259
I didn't mean to offend you.

01:12:07.346 --> 01:12:08.347
Not at all.

01:12:09.697 --> 01:12:12.047
You asked about my ring.

01:12:12.134 --> 01:12:15.006
The truth is
Nick's father had it made

01:12:15.093 --> 01:12:17.792
when he wanted
to propose to me

01:12:17.879 --> 01:12:21.012
because Ah Mawouldn't
give him the family ring.

01:12:21.099 --> 01:12:23.537
I wasn't her first choice.

01:12:23.624 --> 01:12:27.715
Honestly, I wasn't her second.

01:12:27.802 --> 01:12:30.761
Gosh, I'm so sorry.
I had no idea.

01:12:30.848 --> 01:12:32.894
I didn't come
from the right family,

01:12:32.981 --> 01:12:34.678
have the right connections.

01:12:34.765 --> 01:12:36.158
And Ah Mathought
I would not make

01:12:36.245 --> 01:12:37.681
an adequate wife to her son.

01:12:37.768 --> 01:12:40.554
But she came around,
obviously.

01:12:43.339 --> 01:12:45.950
It took many years,

01:12:46.037 --> 01:12:48.692
and she had good reason
to be concerned.

01:12:48.779 --> 01:12:51.869
Because I had no idea
the work

01:12:51.956 --> 01:12:54.916
and the sacrifice
it would take.

01:12:55.003 --> 01:12:57.222
There were many days
when I wondered

01:12:57.309 --> 01:13:00.356
if I would ever measure up.

01:13:00.443 --> 01:13:02.706
But having been through
it all,

01:13:03.968 --> 01:13:05.709
I know this much.

01:13:11.585 --> 01:13:14.022
You will never be enough.

01:13:18.635 --> 01:13:22.639
We should head back.
I wouldn't want Nick to worry.

01:13:38.394 --> 01:13:39.656
You all right?

01:13:40.570 --> 01:13:41.571
Yeah.

